\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.1}{\ignorespaces Comparison of Baseline Vector-Only Retrieval (left) and Implemented Hybrid Retrieval Pipeline (right). The hybrid pipeline adds a metadata filtering stage to reduce the candidate pool and a reranking-lite stage for multi-factor relevance scoring prior to final candidate selection.}}{12}{figure.caption.40}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.2}{\ignorespaces System Context Diagram for TechPulse. Solid arrows represent primary data and query flows; dashed arrows represent monitoring and evaluation signals. The system ingests from five external data sources and serves technology professionals via a query interface, while exposing evaluation and monitoring interfaces.}}{15}{figure.caption.50}%
\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.1}{\ignorespaces Six-Layer Conceptual Architecture of TechPulse. Right-hand solid arrows show the upward ingestion and generation data flow (raw documents $\to $ embeddings $\to $ retrieval $\to $ synthesis $\to $ response). The left-hand dashed arrow shows the downward query path from the user interface to the retrieval layer. Each layer has well-defined responsibilities and interfaces.}}{16}{figure.caption.53}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.2}{\ignorespaces Implemented End-to-End Data Engineering and Serving Pipeline for TechPulse. Five heterogeneous sources feed into the ingestion pipeline. Solid arrows indicate data and control flow; dashed arrows indicate monitoring and observability signals.}}{18}{figure.caption.59}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.3}{\ignorespaces Document State Machine. Each document progresses through four deterministic states. Transition labels show the triggering process (top) and the primary storage destination (bottom). SHA-256 deduplication at ingestion prevents duplicate entries entering the RAW state.}}{20}{figure.caption.63}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.4}{\ignorespaces Entity--Relationship Diagram of the TechPulse PostgreSQL Schema. The \texttt {documents} table stores ingested records; the \texttt {chunks} table stores preprocessed segments with their 384-dimensional pgvector embeddings (HNSW-indexed); and the \texttt {drift\_baselines} table persists drift monitoring history. The \texttt {content\_hash} unique constraint on \texttt {documents} enforces idempotent ingestion.}}{22}{figure.caption.86}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.5}{\ignorespaces Implemented MLOps lifecycle loop: continuous ingestion, preprocessing, indexing, serving, evaluation, and monitoring, with CI/CD automation and a budget governance guard.}}{24}{figure.caption.110}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.6}{\ignorespaces AWS Cloud Deployment Architecture (Learner Lab configuration). Lambda functions, RDS, SQS, and S3 reside within the default VPC. EventBridge schedules ingestion; SQS decouples ingestion from embedding; API Gateway exposes the RAG API to the React frontend. Dashed arrows indicate monitoring and CI/CD flows. The Free Tier configuration replaces the default VPC with a custom VPC, uses custom IAM roles, and enables Amazon Bedrock as the primary LLM backend.}}{27}{figure.caption.126}%
\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.1}{\ignorespaces Evaluation framework: four measurement dimensions, each with a target threshold and the research question it addresses. Arrows point from measurement method to the metric it produces. A Wilcoxon signed-rank test will assess the statistical significance of the precision difference between baseline and hybrid configurations.}}{29}{figure.caption.134}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.2}{\ignorespaces Planned comparison of baseline vs.\ hybrid retrieval across four evaluation dimensions. Bars represent mean scores across 25 evaluation queries. Latency is normalized to the 2-second target (value of 1.0 = target met). Actual values will be populated after evaluation execution.}}{32}{figure.caption.144}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.3}{\ignorespaces Planned grid search results: reranking similarity weight ($\alpha $) vs.\ mean context precision (left axis, solid) and p95 latency (right axis, dashed). The horizontal dashed line marks the 2-second latency constraint. The optimal $\alpha $ maximizes precision without exceeding the latency threshold. Constraint: $\beta = \gamma = (1-\alpha )/2$.}}{32}{figure.caption.146}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.4}{\ignorespaces Planned per-source retrieval distribution for baseline vs.\ hybrid modes. Stacked bars show the proportion of top-$k$ retrieved documents originating from each of the five data sources, averaged across 25 evaluation queries. Greater diversity in the hybrid configuration would support the retrieval hypothesis.}}{33}{figure.caption.148}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.5}{\ignorespaces Planned latency decomposition by pipeline stage for baseline and hybrid retrieval. The baseline omits metadata filtering and reranking stages. The vertical dashed line marks the 2-second p95 latency target. Actual values will be populated from per-query timing measurements.}}{33}{figure.caption.150}%
\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.1}{\ignorespaces TechPulse frontend: hybrid retrieval query with citation-grounded response. The response displays inline source citations and a ranked source list with relevance scores from all five data sources.}}{43}{figure.caption.175}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.2}{\ignorespaces TechPulse frontend: baseline (vector-only) retrieval query on the same question as Figure~\ref {fig:demo_hybrid}, enabling visual comparison of response quality and source diversity.}}{44}{figure.caption.177}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.3}{\ignorespaces Pytest execution: 49 unit tests passing across 5 test modules (\texttt {test\_preprocessing}, \texttt {test\_ingestion}, \texttt {test\_retriever}, \texttt {test\_rag}, \texttt {test\_api}).}}{45}{figure.caption.179}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.4}{\ignorespaces Docker Compose deployment: six services running locally --- PostgreSQL+pgvector, pgAdmin, LocalStack, FastAPI API, React frontend, and the ingestion scheduler.}}{46}{figure.caption.181}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.5}{\ignorespaces GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline: four-stage workflow (lint \& test, Docker build, SAM build, deploy) executing successfully on the \texttt {main} branch.}}{47}{figure.caption.183}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.6}{\ignorespaces pgAdmin: the \texttt {documents} table populated with records from all five data sources (ArXiv, Hacker News, DEV.to, GitHub Trending, RSS), demonstrating successful multi-source ingestion.}}{48}{figure.caption.189}%
\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7.1}{\ignorespaces Project timeline (Gantt chart). Solid bars indicate completed phases; outlined bars indicate remaining work organized into four phases (A--D). The dashed vertical line marks the progress report submission. All remaining work is scheduled to complete by second week of April 2026.}}{53}{figure.caption.222}%
